				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Tipop, you are definately wrong here.
<br />

<br />
It has nothing to do with maturity.  Every person (baring one or two) in my guild has a family, children, is in the working world.
<br />

<br />
DKP is simply the easiest way to apply loot in any situation.  Those who support raids, get first shot at items, and it automatically balances out.
<br />

<br />
NBG just simply will not work for most guilds that raid.  A REBB drops.  Who needs it more?  A monk with Fangs and a GMU, or a beastie with a slp and wlk?  There are simply so many arguments for and against in both directions there and nobody will ever agree to one point of view.  
<br />

<br />
With DKP, the winner has the most points and you push on.<br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=110634" target="_blank" class="postlink">Venerable Isilm</a>
