				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody"></span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Tipop wrote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">
<br />
DKP systems are for guilds with a lot of loot whores and immature kids, I think.</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />

<br />
/agree
<br />

<br />
DKP is horribly inefficient ... almost as bad as pure random as compared to everyone behaving logically and maturely.  In the extreme, to advance efficiently through EQ content, you need to allocate items to a select few rather than wait for them to get enough DKP to beat others on upgrade gear - get your MT with max HPs possible, get FT onto those that need it, and max out melee dps.  I'm sure alot of people get defensive about this, since it 'benefits' the masses more than most other 'methods' - those that freak out about loot can rack up the DKPs and get their 'fix' more frequently than others.
<br />

<br />
However, given the general populace in game, its hard to argue friendly NBG as being superior as one or two flies-in-the-ointment can make it bad for everyone, as in the original post.  You need quite the selection of quality people - I'd have a hard time seeing it being workable on my server, for example.
<br />

<br />
What DKP gives is order however ... there is no need to understand the equipment "plan" to see why you didn't get an item ... there is no need to hope that everyone sees that the item SHOULD go to you.  Thus DKP removes alot of the uncontrollable stresses associated with loot - alot of people make a huge stink about loot distribution.</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
		</table></td>
