			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">The problem with officer assigned or /random NBG on gear is that it tends to lead to the guild placing a lot of pressure, if not outright requirements, to be at any and all raids.  With DKP, you can back off on that, and the guild can be home to more than just the hardcore.  The people who raid the most get more points and will in turn spend it on more items. The people who raid less get fewer points and go longer getting upgrades.
<br />

<br />
Outfitting a "few key people" requires correctly guessing who will be on a lot, who will even stay in the guild, and who will or will not decide to stop playing everquest period.
<br />

<br />
Like the Adventure Points from LDoN, DKP rewards people based on participation.  I personally would rather do that, than institute "thou shalt always drop what thoust are doing to attend the raid call!"  With DKP you make a choice: go on the raid and earn DKP, or don't go and don't get DKP.  If certain raid targets are not getting the "love" that the guild officers and raid leaders want, increase the value of points earned on those raids steadily until more people start attending them.  I may not want anything out of Takish LDoN, but having the faction to get the mid-level armor from MM I certainly have no problem going to Tak for points to spend somewhere else.
<br />

<br />
Same principle raiding.
<br />

<br />
The alternative is people being "AFK" when the raid is called, or "I gotta log, RL calls" to instead play a non-guilded alt, or any of the hundred or so other dodges people have to not raid when they get temporarily burned out or the raid target doesn't drop loot for them or they feel they are likely to be assigned.  I know that, protests of the officers aside, back in my old guild on Saryrn I often felt like a beggar when submitting for loot in an officer-assigned system, while the loot I earn via points in LDoN I take tremendous pride in having *earned.*<br />_________________<br /><span style="font-weight: bold">Venerable Zanros Farwanderer</span> Iksar Feral Lord of Chaotic Rampage, Stromm Server
<br />

<br />
<span style="font-weight: bold">Venerable Zarros Livinglight</span> High Elven Archon, Guildless on Saryrn
<br />

<br />
"Raid? No thanks, don't care for it."</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
		</table></td>
	</tr>
