			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">DKP doesn't always have to as bad as it can be. My guild uses it, and there is often a lot of talk beforehand who wants what, and a lot of the time people skip marginal upgrades if they know somebody could really use some item. And when somebody is annoyed at the loot system (which I've seen happen like 2-3 times during 3 months), he is annoyed at the system, not to any particular person. While this is still bad, it still lessens the guild's inner conflicts.
<br />

<br />
Of course, it's easy to be content about any EP+ guild's loot system if ye are a leather class ... as long as they don't let stuff rot too easily. <img src="images/smiles/icon_wink.gif" alt="Wink" border="0" />
<br />

<br />
</span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Quote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">you need to allocate items to a select few rather than wait for them to get enough DKP to beat others on upgrade gear - get your MT with max HPs possible, get FT onto those that need it, and max out melee dps. </td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />

<br />
That sort of system can implode very easily - seen a guild which concentrated on gearing up their MT and just when they had done that, MT left for an uber guild. Also, it gives the shaft to classes that aren't too high on "raid priority" list, for example beastlords shouldn't get anything really in such a system since our mgb paragon and SD are not gear-dependant and our melee dps is lower than whoever else can use the weapons/vengeance loot. The slower gearing up you get by letting the loot to be distributed more evenly is more than paid off by the fact everybody will be motivated to raid and feel as valuable members of the guild.
<br />

<br />
I remember being angry on my old cleric when "inferior" classes got FT before me, but in the hindsight they had done more to deserve that gear, and I had been far more angry as a shaman if I had done more than a cleric but the FT piece would still have been awarded to the cleric on the grounds the guild needs FT'd clerics more than it needs FT'd shamans.<br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=541294" target="_blank" class="postlink"><img src="http://www.geocities.com/vecna_lives/gach.txt" border="0" /></a></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
		</table></td>
