				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">All systems are flawed because all people are flawed.  Its human nature.  Find what makes you happiest and go with it,  just know it wont always work like you want.  If it bothers you that badly though Id move on.  Hell you can even transfer servers now with all your gear/money so there will be some place that should fit your wants/needs.
<br />

<br />
As far as the druid tunic thing that imho is kinda lame BUT is within the bounderies set.
<br />

<br />
Just like the rogue in a DKP guild who hated one of the warriors in the guild and used his DKP to buy a Bloodfrenzy.  At the time the guilds policy was they are your points use them as you like but dont ever bitch about loot either.  So said rogue would link it to the war on occasion just as a jab.  Childish and immature?  Yes.  But once again within the guidelines set.
<br />

<br />
If your DKP.  Great.  Not all DKP guilds are lootwhore/immature.  They may have a few people that are but so do all guilds :p
<br />

<br />
If your NBG/Officer decisions.  Reward the person not the class.  Nothing I hate more then seeing someone who has a 50% or below raid attendence get an upgrade over someone with 100% when its a decent upgrade for both just because of the class played.</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
