Perhaps it has more to do with our recruitment policies. We never invite someone based on their class or their level. We invite based on friendships. Thus everyone in my guild is interested in the happiness and well-being of the rest of us, and there is very little arguing over loot. In fact, most arguing over loot is more of the "You take it, you can use it more than me." or "No no, I got a nice upgrade last time, you take this one."<br />_________________<br /><br><div align=center><img src="http://www.shootingiron.com/tipop/notherkrag.jpg" width="500" height="200" border="0" usemap="#nothermap"><map name="nothermap"><area alt="Fury of Faith" coords="31,157,152,187" href="http://members.telocity.com/~Tipop2000/fury"><area alt="Tipop's Homepage" coords="186,157,321,187"  href="http://members.telocity.com/~Tipop2000/"><area alt="Kraggan's Magelo Profile" coords="342,157,465,186" href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=120506"></map></div></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
