				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">People willing to work through a DKP system want to content people who are raiding for loot and not for fun only. NBG is closer to fun to my opinion. Notice that on a NBG system, people get upgrades on the same way.
<br />

<br />
There seems to be something weird occuring in EQ.
<br />
People claim that they have friends, and they have. They just seem not be able to outcome a fatal point of number of friends. In larger guilds, one person will have friends, but the whole guild isnt his friend. So he claims for DKP. To be sure not to be cheated it seems. 
<br />

<br />
Now what is this cheated point ?
<br />
ATTENDANCE.
<br />
People think that as very involved in raids, they deserve a stronger reward from what they do. But actually, what are they doing ? They raid more for they have fun playing EQ and raiding bigger things. So basically, they ask to being rewarded for having more fun than others :lol If they are whining about the loot system, its that they dont have fun in doing what they do. Maybe should they change the way they are playing...
<br />
On the other side, NBG isnt based on attendance, but on friendship. NBG people consider their guild and their members as pure friends, and have fun making gifts to others no matter their attendance. Thats something that loot whores / whining attendance people wont ever understand.
<br />

<br />
When people will realize that some of their guildmembers just CANT sacrifice their RL to EQ as they do, they will understand that DKP is a pain in the ass of certain guilds, for some will logically be far better equipped than the others > they will be bored of the basic/current raid targets > they will whine for bigger challenges > they will move ranting ... Would have they give some more casual players some items they had sold for cash only but legally won on DKP system, they would have been able to make the whole guild move with them.
<br />

<br />
Dreamer. I know i am a Dreamer.<br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=258387" target="_blank" class="postlink"><img src="http://c.revol.free.fr/sig.JPG" border="0" /></a>
