NBG fails when things like what started this thread occurs.  It is obvious to the majority that a "clicky" effect is not need.  When you have, in this case, 2 guilds who's definitions of need vary, forget when the individual's definition varies, the system will have issues.  When you're randoming NGB it's a bit of a hybrid system, rather like a DKP guild that has tiers and randoms within those tiers.  Both are improvements over a base ngb where he with the crappiest starter item wins or dkp with he with the most points wins.<br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=110634" target="_blank" class="postlink">Venerable Isilm</a>
