				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I run solo and without a guild for many reasons, the entire above debate is one of the main reasons though.  I've been in guilds that used both and bottom line, IMHO no system will make every person that uses it happy nor will any one system always be fair or in the best interests of all parties involved.
<br />

<br />
If I can't pry it from the cold dead hands of what ever I need to kill for it then I farm the cash and buy it in the bazaar.  That's what works best for me, in the end EQ is a game and it is up to you to find what will work the best for you.
<br />

<br />
In the case where the same druid got both tunics the system obviously did not work.  Your options IMHO are to bring this matter to the attention of the officers of both guilds and if the matter is still not resolved to your satisfaction look for a new guild that works on a system more in line with your personal agenda.
<br />

