			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">DKP systems are the closest thing to fair I've seen.  At least it rewards people for showing up to raids.  Had to quit a guild I was in for over a year because they didn't use any sort of fair system.  They had the officers/raid leader assign loot to people they thought should get it.  That's all fine, but after being in the guild and raiding for over a year, I was awarded absolutely nothing the entire time.  Seemed more like a popularity contest where the people who hung out with the officers the most got all the loot.
<br />

<br />
I don't mind the NBG idea in guilds if the leaders make some effort to be fair about it.  At some point it needs to be a two way street though.  I didn't join a guild for the sole purpose of helping everybody else get nice gear.  I want better gear for myself too.  I don't consider myself a loot whore, but getting awarded nothing after doing god knows how many raids seemed pretty ridiculous to me.  I never bitched about it, maybe that was the problem.  The squeaky wheel gets oiled after all, but there was plenty of loot bitching going on already so I just kept it to myself til I got fed up with getting ignored for loots in every raid.  Hell, I never had any good loot until I went guildless.  At least strangers will roll against you for loot so you've got a chance, that's more than I had with my guild.
<br />

<br />
Anyway, been guildless for almost 2 years including a 1 year break from EQ, and don't care.  I wouldn't even consider a guild that didn't do DKP, or some other system that rewards you for your effort, after my experience with a NBG guild.
<br />

<br />
Guess it doesn't matter too much to me either way though, I found raiding pretty dull anyway.  Killing a mob the first time was fun, killing it 10 more times after that to farm X item that people needed was a drag.  So I don't forsee myself joining a guild of any sort in the near future.</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
