				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I'm starting to see why people have a grudge against NBG. Apparently on your servers it means "The loot goes to whoever needs it the most." I can see how that could cause a lot of arguement, since that can be very subjective. I've never experienced anything like that on my server.
<br />

<br />
On the Karana server, pickup groups are always NBG, and by that we mean "If you can use it and it's an upgrade for you, then you can lotto on it." There's no judgement on who needs it MORE, unless someone decides to bow out because they feel the other person needs it more.
<br />

<br />
So even though we use the same term, it seems we mean two different things when we say "Need Before Greed".<br />_________________<br /><br><div align=center><img src="http://www.shootingiron.com/tipop/notherkrag.jpg" width="500" height="200" border="0" usemap="#nothermap"><map name="nothermap"><area alt="Fury of Faith" coords="31,157,152,187" href="http://members.telocity.com/~Tipop2000/fury"><area alt="Tipop's Homepage" coords="186,157,321,187"  href="http://members.telocity.com/~Tipop2000/"><area alt="Kraggan's Magelo Profile" coords="342,157,465,186" href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=120506"></map></div></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
