				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Tipop's thing where everybody that would use it rolls would have been fine.  Wasn't that way in my guild though, they just decided who it would be best for.
<br />

<br />
I still think DKP is better though.  The whole rolling NBG thing can break down pretty easy.  You've got a chance to get things that way, but maybe you just roll badly and never win.  I'd imagine alot of people would get frustrated with it when they haven't won anything in like 3 months from bad rolls and the person next to them has won 5 straight rolls.  It's certainly better than what I had though.  A pure award based system sucked.
<br />

<br />
DKP really is kinda like the LDoN pts system like somebody else said.  You put in enough time and effort and eventually you get enough pts to buy something.  And both take up a phenomenal amount of your time.  If I'm putting in the time and effort, I want to KNOW that I will get something eventually.  Not just have a chance if I get a lucky roll.</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
